!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Samistore
    /[if lt IE 9]
      <script src="http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    = stylesheet_link_tag    "application", :media => "all"
    = javascript_include_tag "application"
    = csrf_meta_tags
    %meta{:content => "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0", :name => "viewport"}
  %body
    .navbar.navbar-fixed-top
      .navbar-inner
        .container
          %a.btn.btn-navbar{"data-target" => ".nav-collapse", "data-toggle" => "collapse"}
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
          #nav-user-info
            - if user_signed_in?
              = link_to 'Sign out', destroy_user_session_path
            - else
              = link_to 'Sign in', new_user_session_path
          %a.brand{:href => "#"} Sami's Sample Rails Application
          .nav-collapse
          - if user_signed_in?
            %ul.nav
              %li= link_to "Products", products_path
              %li= link_to "Users", users_path #if current_user.roles.name == "Admin"
              %li= link_to "Price List"
              %li= link_to "Contact Us"
              %li= link_to "Cart"
              %li= render "shared/search_form"
          - else
            %ul.nav
              %li= link_to "Products Unavailable"
              
    .container
      .content
        - if flash.present?
          .row
            .span12
              - flash.each do |name, msg|
                = content_tag :div, msg, :id => "flash_#{name}" if msg.is_a?(String)
    .container
      .row
        .span9
          = yield
        .span3
          %h2 About SamiStore
          %p
            %strong This is a sample Rails application demonstrating the following functionality:
          %div -> Uses Haml/PostgreSQL
          %div -> Uses Simple form
          %div -> Product Has Many Discounts/Discount belongs to Product Association
          %div -> Adding and removing discounts for a product
          %div -> Duplicating a product including discounts
          %div -> Filtering by product type
          %div -> Uses has_scope to define scope for filtering
          %div -> Allows tag lists to be added (acts-as-taggable-on)
          %div -> Provides for Uploading of images
          %div -> Dynamic hiding and showing of form sections based on product category selected
          %div -> Conditional model validation for category fields
          %div -> Using Devise for security and authorization
          %div -> Only force password validation if password is blank when creating new user
          %div -> Twitter bootstrap popover (hover) capability
          %div -> PostgreSQL Search
          %div -> Standard seed data
          %div -> Habtm association between users and roles